
    - Angular framework by default provides the form validations.

    - "$error" is the predefined object in Angular Framework.

    - "$error" stores the form related errors.

    - if any error raised in form , automatically framework

      stores the error into "$error" object.

user name validation (text validation).
-
<form name="myForm">
    <input type="text"
           name="uname"
           ng-model="uname"
           ng-minlength="3"
           ng-maxlength="6"
           required>
    <h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.minlength">***Minimum 3 charcters are required***</h5>
    <h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.maxlength">***Maximum 6 characters are allowd***</h5>
    <h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.required">***Can't Left Blank***</h5>
</form>


email validation.

<input  type="email"
        name="uemail"
        required>


<h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uemail.$error.required">***Can't Left Blank***</h5>
<h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uemail.$error.email">***Please Enter the Valid Email***</h5>


phone number validation
-
<input type="text"
       name="uphone"
       required
       ng-pattern="/^(\+\d{1,3}[- ]?)?\d{10}$/">
<h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uphone.$error.required">***Can't Left Blank***</h5>
<h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uphone.$error.pattern">***Please enter the valid mobile no***</h5>



Validations by using neMessages Module.

    - by using ngMessages module we can overcome the data redundency.

    - by using ngMessages module we can reuse the Validation Messages.


download the mgMessages Module.

    > bower install angular-messages --save

Path Given by bower.
"bower_components/ angular-messages / angular-messages.min.js"









